Run Haplogrep on African Samples

This R-Markdown script runs over all genotyping arrays based on the publication from Lankheet et al 2021 https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34674637/. Thereby we calculate the haplogroups based on the present genotypes per microarray and calculate the distance to the resulting haplogroups from the sequencing data (n=193). The result is a ranked list, based on the area under the curve (AUC) for the empirical cumulative distribution function (ECDF).

Interpretability: An array that has a distance of 0 for every sample would have an ECDF value of 1.0 at every point from 0 to 26, resulting in a maximum AUC of 27. The ECDF value at any distance \(x\) is \(P(Distance \le x)\). By averaging these probabilities across the whole range, we are calculating the expected probability that a sample falls within the acceptable range at any given cutoff.

Comparability: A score of 0.95 instantly shows that the array is performing at 95% of its theoretical maximum efficiency regarding haplogroup calling accuracy.
